m1dd x2c h13 y251 ff2 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">controversy, Lucifer rebelled against God by questioning the neces-</div><div class="t m23b x2c h13 y252 ff2 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sity of obeying His law. </div><div class="t m23c x48 h11 y253 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What position did Jesus take regarding the law? </div><div class="t m23d x48 h11 y254 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Matt. 5:17, 18 (what Jesus taught) </div><div class="t m42 x24 h11 y254 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m21b x93 h11 y254 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m23e x48 h11 y255 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">John 15:10 (Jesus&apos; testimony) </div><div class="t m42 x60 h11 y255 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m21b x93 h11 y255 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m23f x48 h11 y97 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2 Cor. 5:21; 1 Pet. 2:22 (the sinlessness of Jesus) </div><div class="t m240 x11 h11 y256 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The nature of a government is discerned by its laws: Evil </div><div class="t m241 x12 h11 y257 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">governments have evil laws; good governments have good laws. </div><div class="t m242 x12 h11 y9f ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In this context, what does it mean to say that God&apos;s law is a </div><div class="t m243 x12 h11 y258 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;transcript of His character&quot;? (see </div><div class="t m244 x24 h11 y259 ff6 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Great Controversy, </div><div class="t m6e x94 h11 y259 ff5 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. 434). </div><div class="t m245 x8d h13 y25a ff2 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">15 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
